older women participated in workshops that offered them the opportunity and encouragement to reflect on and create written records of their lives. With Courage and Common Sense presents an extensive selection of memoirs from the OWL Circle project. Organized thematically, they describe women's experiences of identity, place, work, family life, love and marriage, loss and healing, adventures great and small, major historical events, and legacies to keep and pass along. Taken as a whole, the memoirs chronicle far-reaching changes in the ways that women participated in the world during the twentieth century. They show how women learned to surmount obstacles, to courageously make the most of the opportunities that came their way, and to move quietly and wisely beyond the limits that were imposed upon them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAutobiographieszTexas. 0aBiography as a literary form. 0aBiographyy20th century. 0aOlder womenzTexasvBiography. 0aWomenzTexasvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aAlbert, Susan Wittig, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCarpenter, Liz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarpenter, Liz.1 aFinet, Dayna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292796553423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292796553/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK